Molecular analysis . To estimate the evolutionary divergence between the studied
Luciobarbus
groups across the Aegean Basin, we downloaded 15 already existing COI sequences from NCBI GenBank (listed in Table 1 ), where they were deposited by
. After aligning the DNA barcodes sequences by MUSCLE (
), we calculated the uncorrected pairwise genetic distances (p-distances), i.e. the number of base differences per site from between sequences using MEGA 11 (
). A gamma distribution (shape parameter = 5) was used to model the rate variation between sites in this analysis. Codon positions included were 1st+2nd+3rd+noncoding. All positions with less than 98% site coverage were eliminated. This meant that less than 2% alignment gaps, missing data and ambiguous bases were allowed at any position (partial deletion option).
